1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1151.2, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 1151.2. As used in the Roofing Contractor Registration
4 Act:
5 1. "Advertise" means any written publication, dissemination,
6 solicitation, contract, bid, promotional item, or circulation which
7 is intended to directly or indirectly induce any person to contract
8 for roofing construction services with the advertiser, including,
9 but not limited to, business cards, telephone directory display
10 advertisements, vehicle signage, radio, television and electronic
11 solicitations;
12 2. "Applicant" means the qualifying party, or if no qualifying
13 party, any person applying under the Roofing Contractor Registration
14 Act for a roofing contractor registration to be issued by the
15 Construction Industries Board;
16 3. "Board" means the Construction Industries Board;
17 4. "Committee" means the Committee of Roofing Examiners;
18 5. "Homeowner" means one who owns and resides in, or who
19 resides in, or who contracts for the purchase, construction,
20 remodeling or repairing of a residence;
21 6. "Nonresident contractor" means any contractor who has not
22 established and maintained a place of business as a roofing
23 contractor in this state within the preceding year, or who claims
24
Req. No. 15702 Page 3

1 resi dency in another state, or who has not submitted an income tax
2 return as a resident of this state within the preceding year;
3 7. "Owner" means the person who owns the property or is a
4 lessee of the property;
5 8. "Person" means any natural person, firm, limited or general
6 partnership, corporation, association, limited liability company,
7 trust, association, other legal entity and any organization capable
8 of conducting business, or any combination thereof acting as a unit,
9 unless the intent to give a more limited meaning is disclosed
10 clearly by the Roofing Contractor Registration Act;
11 9. "Prime contractor" means a general contractor, commercial
12 contractor, or other contractor who contracts directly with the
13 owner for construction trade work in covering multiple trade areas
14 and engages endorsed contractors to perform the work as required by
15 law, and who does not advertise for endorsed contractor work unless
16 he or she are endorsed for the work as required by law;
17 10. "Project manager" means one who manages construction
18 projects consisting of work involving multiple trades;
19 11. "Public contract" means a contract with the State of
20 Oklahoma, its political subdivisions, or any board, commission, or
21 department thereof, or with any board of county commissioners, or
22 with any city council, school board, or with any state or municipal
23 agency, or with any other public board, body, commission, or agency
24 authorized to award contracts for the construction or reconstruction
