1 of p ublic works and includes subcontracts undertaken to perform
2 works covered by the original contract or any part thereof;
3 12. "Qualifying party" means a natural individual person who is
4 a registrant and an officer or owner of the corporation, a member of
5 the limited liability company, or a general partner of the limited
6 liability partnership, and who is actively engaged in the work
7 undertaken by the registrant roofing contractor work for which a
8 registration is required pursuant to the Roofing Contractor
9 Registration Act who meets the experience and ability requirements
10 for registration on behalf of the registrant associated with and
11 responsible for all roofing contractor work of such entity;
12 13. "Registrar" means the Construction Industries Board or any
13 person designated by the Board to administer the provisions of the
14 Roofing Contractor Registration Act;
15 14. "Registration" means the process of applying for an initial
16 or renewal registration which upon approval is exhibited by a
17 registration number and card issued to a qualifying party pursuant
18 to the Roofing Contractor Registration Act;
19 15. "Registration number" means the roofing registration number
20 issued to a qualifying party by the registrar to the registrant's
21 qualifying party;
22 16. "Registrant" means a holder of a roofing registration
23 issued pursuant to the Roofing Contractor Registration Act and is
24
