1 the qualifying party unless any required endorsement is in inactive
2 endorsee status;
3 17. "Residence" means a single structure for residential
4 occupancy or use which is a detached one- to four-family dwelling or
5 a multiple single-family dwelling (townhouse) not more than three
6 stories/floors above grade plane in height with a separate means of
7 egress, and any appurtenances thereto, which is intended for use as
8 a primary habitation and is in compliance with the International
9 Residential Code, as adopted by the Oklahoma Uniform Building Code
10 Commission;
11 18. "Roofing contractor" means any person, including a
12 subcontractor and nonresident contractor, engaged in the business of
13 commercial or residential roofing contractor work, or who himself or
14 herself, or through another, attempts to or advertises, holds
15 himself or herself out as having, or purports to have, the capacity
