8 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1151.3, is
9 amended to read as follows:
10 Section 1151.3 A. All roofing contractors shall be registered
11 annually by the Board. All registrations shall be nontransferable.
12 It is unlawful for any person to act as a roofing contractor without
13 having a current and valid roofing contractor's registration or act
14 as a commercial or residential roofing contractor without a current
15 and valid commercial roofer endorsement issued pursuant to the
16 Roofing Contractor Registration Act, unless the person is exempt
17 under the Roofing Contractor Registration Act. Evidence of securing
18 a permit, including roofing work from a governmental agency or the
19 employment of a person on a roofing project, shall be accepted in
20 any court as prima facie evidence of the existence of a contract.
21 Engaging in or offering to engage in work without a valid
22 registration and active commercial or residential roofer endorsement
23 as required for roofing contractors or performing roofing services
24 during any period when the roofing contractor's registration is
Req. No. 15702 Page 17

1 deni ed, not in good standing, expired, suspended, or revoked or when
2 the required endorsement is not active is a violation of the Roofing
3 Contractor Registration Act. Subcontracting roofing work to an
4 unregistered or unendorsed roofer or improperly endorsed roofing
5 contractor when the work requires an active endorsement is a
6 violation of this act. Failure to provide proof to the registrar on
7 the jobsite of the active current and properly endorsed qualifying
8 party directly supervising the job is a violation of the Roofing
9 Contractor Registration Act for which enforcement action may be
10 taken on each person performing roofing work on the jobsite and each
11 subcontractor up to and including the contractor contracting
12 directly with the owner.
13 Each copy of a roofing contractor's record, which would include
14 responses to any complaints, that is from and verified by the
15 registrar, or a verified statement from the registrar that there is
16 no record as no application was made, shall be received in all
17 courts in this state as prima facie evidence of the facts stated
18 therein.
19 A verified copy of a roofing contractor's administrative
20 citation for unregistered activity or without required commercial or
21 residential roofer endorsement and order of final disposition from
22 the registrar shall be received in all courts in this state as prima
23 facie evidence of the facts stated therein, including establishment
24 thereby of the first offense.
