19 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1151.4, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 1151.4. The Construction Industries Board is authorized
22 to administer the Roofing Contractor Registration Act. In addition
23 to the powers stated in the Construction Industries Board Act, the
24 Board shall have the following powers:
Req. No. 15702 Page 22

1 1. Exercise all incidental powers and duties necessary to
2 effectuate the provisions of the Roofing Contractor Registration
3 Act;
4 2. Promulgate, adopt, amend, suspend and repeal rules as may be
5 reasonably necessary to effectuate the provisions of the Roofing
6 Contractor Registration Act, the proper performance of its duties,
7 and to define categories and limitations for such registration and
8 endorsement. The rule-making powers of the Construction Industries
9 Board are subject to the Administrative Procedure Act, including
10 those pertaining to emergency or temporary rules or regulations;
