16 roofing contractor work in this state and who are registered
17 pursuant to the Roofing Contractor Registration Act, and otherwise
18 meet all requirements for endorsement in this act; and
19 5. One member shall be appointed by the Construction Industries
20 Board and shall be a licensed or certified building and construction
21 inspector who is a member of a statewide organization representing
22 certified building inspectors with a minimum of five (5) years'
23 actual job experience in building code inspections. This member
24 shall be selected from a list of at least three qualified and
Req. No. 15702 Page 69

1 elig ible inspectors submitted by a state organization representing
2 inspectors.
3 C. Any vacancy on the Committee shall be filled for the
4 unexpired term as soon as possible in the manner in which that
5 position was originally filled. Members shall continue in office
6 until a successor is appointed by the appointing authority. The
7 appointing authority shall fill all vacancies and unexpired terms in
8 the same manner as the original appointment of the member whose
9 position is to be filled. Such members may be removed by the
10 appointing authority at any time.
11 D. A majority of the Committee shall constitute a quorum for
12 the transaction of business, and the Committee shall elect a chair
13 from its number. Each member shall receive reimbursement for travel
14 expenses in accordance with the provisions of the State Travel
15 Reimbursement Act. The Committee shall meet at least quarterly, and
16 special meetings may be called by the Committee chair or the Board.
17 SECTION 20. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1151.27, is
