19 SECTION 21. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1151.28, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 1151.28. A. The designee of the Construction
22 Industries Board, as chair, and the Committee of Roofing Examiners
23 shall act as the Roofing Hearing Board and shall comply with the
24
Req. No. 15702 Page 73

1 prov isions of the Construction Industries Board Act, rules and
2 Article II of the Administrative Procedures Act.
3 B. Any administrative hearing on suspensions, revocations or
4 fines shall be conducted by a hearing examiner appointed by the
5 Construction Industries Board. The hearing examiner's decision
6 shall be a final decision which may be appealed to a district court
7 in accordance with the Administrative Procedures Act and the
8 Construction Industries Board Act and rules and regulations.
9 C. The Roofing Hearing Board may, upon its own motion, and
10 shall, upon written complaint filed by any person, investigate and
11 conduct hearings on the business transactions of any roofing
12 contractor, firm or any person soliciting or engaging in roofing
13 contractor work.
14 D. The Roofing Hearing Board may conduct hearings on citations
15 issued to any person pursuant to the Roofing Contractor Registration
16 Act, applications for suspension and revocation of a registration or
17 endorsement.
18 E. The Construction Industries Board shall suspend or revoke or
19 may refuse to issue or renew any license or registration under the
20 commercial or residential roofer endorsement provisions of the
21 Roofing Contractor Registration Act for any of the following
22 standards of the Roofing Contractor Registration Act:
23 1. Making a material misstatement in the application for an
24 registration, endorsement, or the renewal of an endorsement;
Req. No. 15702 Page 74

1 2. Obtaining any registration or endorsement by false or
2 fraudulent representation;
3 3. Loaning or allowing the use of such registration or
4 endorsement by any other person or illegally using a registration or
5 an endorsement;
6 4. Demonstrating incompetence to act as a commercial or
7 residential roofing contractor or Labor-only crew;
8 5. Violating any provisions of the Roofing Contractor
9 Registration Act, or any rule or order prescribed by the
10 Construction Industries Board pursuant to the provisions of the
11 Roofing Contractor Registration Act; or
12 6. Willfully failing to perform normal business obligations
13 without justifiable cause.
14 F. Any person whose endorsement or registration has been
15 revoked by the Roofing Hearing Board may apply for a new license one
16 (1) year from the date of such revocation.
17 SECTION 22. REPEALER Section 5, Chapter 368, O.S.L.
18 2025, is hereby repealed.
19 SECTION 23. This act shall become effective January 1, 2027.
